{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:37:15.483Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the available technical resources and community discussions about Claude Computer Use, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Coordinate systems and viewport management\""},{"type":"text","text":" refers to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"the pixel-based coordinate space where Claude operates when clicking, typing, and scrolling"},{"type":"text","text":" — including how the system defines screen dimensions, handles coordinate mapping between captured screenshots and actual display, and manages viewport scaling to ensure actions land at the correct positions."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core Coordinate System"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pixel-Based Cartesian Grid"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Coordinates are in pixel units (x, y) on a 2D Cartesian grid"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"action\": \"click\",\n  \"coordinate\": [342, 156]  // x=342 pixels, y=156 pixels\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Origin position"},{"type":"text","text":": Standard screen coordinate system with origin at "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"(0, 0)"},{"type":"text","text":" (top-left corner)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Display Dimensions Configuration"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Python: Define display dimensions\ntool = {\n    \"type\": \"computer_20241022\",\n    \"name\": \"computer\",\n    \"display_width_px\": 1024,  # Width in pixels\n    \"display_height_px\": 768   # Height in pixels\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reference dimensions"},{"type":"text","text":": The documentation uses "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"display_width: 1024, display_height: 768"},{"type":"text","text":" as the example."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coordinate Mapping Problem"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Viewport Challenge"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Community issue"},{"type":"text","text":": \"I'm getting responses from the API, but I'm having issues where the coordinates I get back from eg a click event don't correspond to my viewport\"."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Problem:\nClaude returns coordinates → Your viewport has different dimensions → Click lands wrong"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Root cause"},{"type":"text","text":": \"You're right, the documentation doesn't mention anything about having to normalize coordinates\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Standardization vs Actual Dimensions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key discovery"},{"type":"text","text":": \"I took a guess that the response coordinates were for a standardized "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1024x1024 image"},{"type":"text","text":" and it looks like that was correct\"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Solution workflow"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Claude returns coordinates based on standardized 1024x1024 image\n   ↓\n2. You need to map to your actual viewport dimensions\n   ↓\n3. Translate from 1024x1024 to your viewport (e.g., 1920x1080)\n   ↓\n4. Click lands at correct position"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coordinate Transformation"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mapping Formula"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Window to viewport mapping"},{"type":"text","text":" (from graphics principles):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Given:\n- Window coordinates: (x, y) in 1024x1024 standardized space\n- Viewport: (x_min, y_min) to (x_max, y_max) in actual screen\n\nTransformed coordinates (x1, y1):\n    x1 = (x - x_min) * (V_width / W_width) + x_min\n    y1 = (y - y_min) * (V_height / W_height) + y_min"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Where"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"W_width = 1024"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"W_height = 1024"},{"type":"text","text":" (standardized window)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"V_width = actual viewport width"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"V_height = actual viewport height"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"x_min = 0"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"y_min = 0"},{"type":"text","text":" (top-left origin)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simplified mapping"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"def map_coordinates(clause_x, clause_y, viewport_width, viewport_height):\n    \"\"\"Map from 1024x1024 standardized space to actual viewport\"\"\"\n    scale_x = viewport_width / 1024.0\n    scale_y = viewport_height / 1024.0\n    \n    actual_x = int(clause_x * scale_x)\n    actual_y = int(clause_y * scale_y)\n    \n    return (actual_x, actual_y)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example Transformation"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Claude returns coordinates from 1024x1024 standardized space\nclaude_x = 512  # Center of standardized image\nclaude_y = 512\n\n# Your actual viewport is 1920x1080\nviewport_width = 1920\nviewport_height = 1080\n\n# Map to actual coordinates\nscale_x = 1920 / 1024.0  # 1.875\nscale_y = 1080 / 1024.0  # 1.055\n\nactual_x = int(512 * 1.875)  # 960 pixels\nactual_y = int(512 * 1.055)  # 540 pixels\n\n# Click at (960, 540) on your 1920x1080 screen"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Viewport Management"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Is a Viewport"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Viewport definition"},{"type":"text","text":": \"A rectangular region of the screen where the contents of the window are displayed\"."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"World coordinate system (application) → Window (selected area) → Viewport (screen area) → Device coordinates (actual screen)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Viewport Challenges in Computer Use"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenge"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Impact"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Different dimensions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude learns on 1024x1024, your screen may be 1920x1080"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aspect ratio mismatch"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Distortion when mapping between spaces"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tilted images"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perspective shifts all coordinates"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Window position changes"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coordinate drift (window moves on screen)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[aitoolsguidebook](https://aitoolsguidebook.com/en/articles/claude-computer-use-action-loop/)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices for Viewport"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Best practice: Use dimensions from the example\ndisplay_width = 1024\ndisplay_height = 768\n\n# Or normalize to your actual viewport\nactual_width = 1920\nactual_height = 1080\n\n# Map coordinates before executing action\nactual_x, actual_y = map_coordinates(clause_x, clause_y, actual_width, actual_height)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Recommendation"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Try to stick with the dimensions in the example (1024x768)\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Grounding Issues"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coordinate Drift"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Problem"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Coordinate drift: window position changes\"."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scenario:\n1. Click at (342, 156) on window\n2. User moves window on screen\n3. Same coordinates now point to wrong location"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Solution"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Detect screenshot differences or add explicit state checks\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual Perspective Issues"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Problem"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Features that shift model's perspective\"."}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cause"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Effect"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tilted images"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All coordinates scaled and rotated"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Framed images"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perspective distortion"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3D perspective"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model misinterprets depth"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[community.openai](https://community.openai.com/t/how-are-the-computer-use-api-coordinates-calculated/1143891)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Action Types and Coordinates"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coordinate Usage by Action"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coordinate Usage"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"click"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Click at (x, y) in viewport"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"type"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No coordinate (types at current cursor)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"scroll"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scroll at (x, y) by (dx, dy) pixels"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"key"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No coordinate (global key press)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[platform.claude](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/agents-and-tools/tool-use/computer-use-tool)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Debugging Coordinate Issues"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Diagnostic Steps"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Step 1: Extract known points from screenshot\nknown_points = [\n    {\"label\": \"top-left\", \"x\": 0, \"y\": 0},\n    {\"label\": \"center\", \"x\": 512, \"y\": 512},  # 1024x1024 center\n    {\"label\": \"bottom-right\", \"x\": 1024, \"y\": 1024},\n]\n\n# Step 2: Find transformation matrix\n# Map from Claude's 1024x1024 space to your viewport\ntransform_matrix = find_transformation(known_points, your_viewport)\n\n# Step 3: Apply to all coordinates\nactual_x, actual_y = apply_transform(clause_x, clause_y, transform_matrix)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Fixes"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Fix 1: Stick to example dimensions\ndisplay_width = 1024\ndisplay_height = 768\n\n# Fix 2: Normalize to your viewport\nactual_x = int(clause_x * (actual_width / 1024))\nactual_y = int(clause_y * (actual_height / 1024))\n\n# Fix 3: Improve prompt coherence\nprompt = \"Click the login button at the top-right corner\"  # More specific\n\n# Fix 4: Avoid illusion/detractors\n# - Use straight-on screenshots (no tilt)\n# - Remove distracting visual elements\n# - Ensure clear, non-ambiguous UI"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of coordinate systems like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"camera photography"},{"type":"text","text":": Claude's standardized 1024x1024 is like the camera's sensor (fixed resolution). Your actual viewport (1920x1080) is like the printed photo (different size). When Claude says \"click at (512, 512)\" on the sensor, you need to scale it to the photo's dimensions. If you print a 100mm photo and Claude says \"50mm from left,\" you'd click at 50mm. But if you print a 200mm photo, that same 50mm becomes 100mm. The relation is the same (center), but the absolute position changes based on viewport size."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coordinates: pixel units (x, y) on 2D Cartesian grid, origin at (0, 0) top-left"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Standardized space: Claude returns coordinates based on "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1024x1024 standardized image"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Display dimensions: configure "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"display_width_px: 1024, display_height_px: 768"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Problem: \"coordinates don't correspond to my viewport\" — need normalization"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mapping formula: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"actual_x = int(clause_x * (viewport_width / 1024))"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"actual_y = int(clause_y * (viewport_height / 1024))"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: 512 in 1024x1024 → 960 in 1920x1080 (scale factor 1.875x, 1.055x)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Viewport: rectangular region of screen where window contents are displayed"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Issues: different dimensions, aspect ratio mismatch, tilted images, window position changes"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coordinate drift: window moves → same coordinates point to wrong location"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual perspective: tilted/framed images cause coordinate scaling and rotation"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practice: Use dimensions from example (1024x768) or normalize to your viewport"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Debug: extract known points, find transformation matrix, apply to all coordinates"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Action coordinates: click uses (x, y), scroll uses (x, y) + (dx, dy), type/key use no coordinate"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"You're right, the documentation doesn't mention anything about having to normalize coordinates\" — the key insight is that Claude operates on standardized 1024x1024 space, and you must map those coordinates to your actual viewport dimensions before executing actions."}]}]}}
